sentence: The Home Depot, Inc. ( HD ) is due to issue its quarterly earnings report in the upcoming extended-hours session.
Given its history, traders can expect very active trading in the issue immediately following its quarterly earnings announcement.

Historical earnings event related premarket and after-hours trading activity in HD indicates that the price change in the extended hours is likely to be of limited value in forecasting additional price movement by the following regular session close.

Over the prior three fiscal years (12 quarters), when shares of HD rose in the extended-hours session in reaction to its earnings announcement, history shows that 50.0% of the time (5 events) the stock posted additional gains in the following regular session by an average of 1.7%.
There are no earnings events over the previous 12 quarters with extended-hours price reactions in this direction.
Data provided by the MT Pro service at MTNewswires.com.
